A former Minister of Education, Alhaji Muhammad Bello Dogondaji, has passed on at the age of 84. He died Friday at the Usman Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital, Sokoto following a brief illness, a  statement signed by Hassan Bello on behalf of the family disclosed. According to him, the late Santurakin Sokoto was diagnosed with stroke and admitted in the intensive care unit (ICU). He died six hours after admission in the ICU, Hassan Bello added. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Muhammad Bello Dogondaji is survived by wives, 17 children and several grandchildren. Alhaji Bello who commenced his career as an administrator and educationist, attended Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria and the University of Birmingham. He served in many state and federal capacities culminating in his appointment as Minister of Education between January 1993 and January 1994. The statement noted that the descendant of the Sokoto Caliphate was a pillar of its traditional institutions. It prayed  Allah to forgive his trespasses and bestow the everlasting peace and bountiful gift of Aljannat Firdausi on his sublime dignity and humble soul. Former Governor of old Sokoto state, Nadama dies at 87; Tambuwal mourns Adamu Ciroma passes on at 84 Students urged to emulate Sardauna, uphold unity